service.name: Midwife Professional Indemnity Scheme - Run-Off Cover Commonwealth Contributions (Claims Scheme)
service.description: The Midwife Professional Indemnity Scheme - Run-Off Cover Commonwealth Contributions (Claims Scheme) (ROC) is designed to assist an eligible Insurer in respect of claims made against midwives who are retired; were not engaged in private practice during the preceding 3 years; have a permanent disability; are deceased; are on maternity leave, or have permanently left private midwifery practice in Australia. ROC Commonwealth contributions reimburse the Insurer 100% of an eligible claim. Under the ROC scheme eligible claims will be paid by the Australian Government.  A levy placed on total premium costs is payable by the Insurer annually.  Levies collected will fund midwife Run-off Cover claims.

Dimension.name: Midwife Professional Indemnity Scheme
